label: Suara Karya
title: Suara_Karya
exrest: Suara Karya was a daily newspaper published in Indonesia. Established in 1971 to assist Golkar in winning that year's legislative election, it became required reading for all civil servants and the voice of Golkar. After its circulation increased from 55,700 in 1971 to 300,000 in 1998, the fall of Suharto's dictatorship caused circulation to plummet to 3,000. As of 2005, it is attempting rebranding to present cleaner, less biased news.
